r‚ÜêGet req;folder;resolved;status
‚çù REST GET handler restricted to /files against AppState.RootFolder. The
‚çù optional folder query parameter is resolved via ResolveSubfolder - the
‚çù only function permitted to turn client-supplied path text into a
‚çù filesystem path - before CheckFolder classifies the result. The raw
‚çù byte-serving /file endpoint is added in a later issue; any other
‚çù endpoint is a 404. An unexpected failure inside BuildListingResponse
‚çù (for instance the resolved folder being unreadable, or removed after
‚çù Get resolved it) becomes a clean 500 rather than a stack trace reaching
‚çù the client.
 :If req.Endpoint‚â¢'/files'
     r‚Üêreq.Fail 404
     ‚Üí0
 :EndIf
 folder‚Üê(req.QueryParams[;1]‚ç≥‚äÇ'folder')‚äÉreq.QueryParams[;2],‚äÇ''
 resolved‚ÜêAppState.RootFolder ResolveSubfolder folder
 :If resolved‚â°'outside-root'
     r‚Üêreq.Fail 400
     ‚Üí0
 :EndIf
 status‚ÜêCheckFolder resolved
 :Select status
 :Case 'not-found'
     r‚Üêreq.Fail 404
 :Case 'not-a-directory'
     :If resolved‚â°AppState.RootFolder
         r‚Üêreq.Fail 500
     :Else
         r‚Üêreq.Fail 404
     :EndIf
 :Else
     :Trap 0
         r‚ÜêBuildListingResponse resolved
     :Else
         r‚Üêreq.Fail 500
     :EndTrap
 :EndSelect
